<br>
Freeport.  I am in Freeport.  And if I am to survive, I best find something to weigh down my purse a bit.<br>
<br>
But that dream.  I had it again last night.  More vivid than before.  Perhaps it is some sort of message.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
I am standing in the middle of a barren plain.  The vastness and emptiness of it is suffocating.  An overwhelming feeling of being lost and alone comes over me.  I run around aimlessly trying to find anything on this featureless landscape, but nothing yeilds it's presense.  I sit down and turn inward on myself, trying to shut out the world, when a shadow falls over me.<br>
<br>
I spring up in a start to find that I am not alone.  An old man stands over me, holding a staff to his side.  No, not a man, an elf, definately pure elf blood.  Yet he is featureless, and unlike any elf I've seen.  A sense of power, terribly destructive is about him.  Yet, something else, too.  A very warming feeling, such that I feel like I should know him, like he is the father I never knew.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> I checked my pouch, and snacked sparingly on the bits of food in there.  If I could not get some coin, this would have to last awhile.  Taking a swig of ale, I returned to pondering the dream.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
The elf put his hand on my head, and it was very comforting, chasing away my feelings of being alone, replacing it with a feeling of belonging, and a feeling of being important.  I started to look up, when a strong wind picked up, and I had to sheild my eyes from the dust and the rain.<br>
<br>
The rain, there is a storm in the direction the man had been, pouring torrential rains down in it's wake.  A river forms out of the storm.  Grass sprouts out of the ground, trees grow, and a few animal calls can be heard.  I walk into the storm, yet do not get wet.  The rain is heavy all around, yet beyond I can see the glow of the setting sun.  But the sun looks closer than the sunset I fell asleep to.<br>
<br>
Overhead I hear the fluttering of wings.  I look up in time to see a crow winging past.  It caws 3 times, or is it a caw?  I wake up to the sound of someone shouting nearby.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Returning the contents of the pouch to their place, I get ready to depart for the day.  What does the dream mean?  What could it be?  Perhaps I shall go to the scholars of Erudin to get insight, I hear some of them analyze dreams.<br>
<br>
So it is settled, I set out for the west today.  I guess I will have to take a few shortcuts to a few coin, where it will not be missed.  To the west... towards the setting sun?</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=mithlin>Mithlin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/10/02 9:03:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=350.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Chilling Battle</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> What a chill breeze in the air.  Something about the cold here just seems to bore straight through a person, more than just cold.  I am cold yet completely drenched in sweat.  I had the dream again, though somehow darker than before, like the evil I can feel in this place is oozing into my dreams.  But still, the further west I trudge, the stronger I feel the calling.  Surely, this dream was even more clear than the last.  It frustrates me to not know the meaning of the dream, yet I feel must follow it.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
There is blackness everywhere.  Utter blackness all around me.  My breath comes in shallow gasps, as I reach out, trying to feel anything.  There is nothing out there, yet I feel terribly afraid.  Frantic, I probe all around me with my hands, but there is nothing.  A feeling of terror comes over me, like I am being watched by unfriendly eyes.  My pulse races, and I am in complete panic.  There has not been even the slightest hint of danger.  The sense of some great evil about to strike comes suddenly in a rush, like a wave.  Panic gets the better of my sense and I run.  I do not know where I am running to, but I feel I must get away from where I am.  As fast as I can go, not looking back, not even thinking about what is back there.  I do not get more than a handful of paces, though it seems like years it took me to get there, when I lose my footing and fall.  Reaching out to regain my step, my hand runs into something.  No, not something, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> somebody</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  I am completely overtaken by panic.<br>
<br>
Laying face down in a field of lush green grass, I look up.  The sky is a nice blue, with wispy clouds overhead.  Green grass extends on the smooth unbroken plains as far as the eye can see.  Off in the distance I hear thunder.  A light breeze teases at my hair.  Standing in front of me is the same old elf from my other dreams, and my hand is on his leg.  I feel silly with my hand on him, yet somehow the touch is comforting.  Not that I need any comforting right now, in such nice surroundings as this.  But the comfort is relaxing, and I am hesitant to pull away.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> The wind howls in the trees outside.  Or is it the wind?  I can't really tell.  Dawn is still an hour or two away, but I fear sleep shall not claim me again in this cursed woods.<br>
<br>
After making a few stops in Freeport, I traveled most of the day.  I got into Kithicor Forest as the sun was getting low, so I started looking for a place to stay.  Quite a few doors I came across were locked and barred, lending to the general feeling of unease of the place.  Finally I found an inn that would admit me, though the keeper only unbarred the door long enough to hastily get me inside, then barred it again.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Moving my hand, I stand up, the old elf smiles at me.  Suddenly, he doubles over as if in pain, and his features seem to be trying to shift.  For a moment, he seems almost to look like he has the dark skin of the fallen elven race.  The image does not stick, but rather constantly shifts between the warm caring old elf and a cruel grotesque dark elf.  I reach in to try and help, but as soon as I touch his skin, I am blast backward by a force of energy.<br>
<br>
I am dazed for a few seconds, just staring up at the clouds drifting by overhead.  Inside myself I can feel the same struggle going on nearby in the elf.  The feeling passes and I am able to stand up.  There is no sign that the elf, nor his internal struggle, had ever been nearby.  I look around at the nearby hills, trying to find some sign of life.  But the rolling fields of grass are unbroken, waving gently in the occasional gust of wind.<br>
<br>
The clouds pass overhead, driven by some unfelt wind.  The more I notice them pass the more I feel as if they are tugging on me, urging me to follow their progression through the sky.  Following the clouds, I seem to float over the fields of grass.  The distant hills do not ever seen to get closer, yet I feel as if I am going in the right direction.  I notice a black dot in the cloudy sky.  Straining against it, I discover it is a crow flying towards me.  The crow lands in a nearby tree and looks at me.  It caws three times, or is it a caw?  I wake up to the sound of an evil screech outside.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Huddling in my bedding, I sit fearing to hear that sound again that woke me from my dream.  It does not come again, but I do hear other chilling sounds around.<br>
<br>
This dark accursed forest does not give any comfort.  I doubt I shall ever stay here again.  Yet still, I feel the pulling west even stronger than before, and that eases my worries some.  I shall be glad when sunrise comes and the light chases the dark away.  The sooner I can get out of Kithicor Forest, the better.  I still do not know the meaning of my dream, but I am certain that something about this place has fouled tonight’s dream.  It is as if there are two warring forces.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
