</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=mithlin>Mithlin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/22/02 5:36:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=350.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Short Comings</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  A rest will be nice after a long day’s journey across the plains of Karana.  The weather cleared up nicely and was most welcoming to a traveler, though a light rain is starting to pick up now.  There is just one more leg of the journey, the boat ride from Qeynos to Erudin.  Finally I will be able to get my questions answered.  Maybe.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
The gates of Qeynos are quite a welcome sight in the distance.  The sun is starting to approach the horizon, so I think I will stay the night in Qeynos before finishing my journey to Erudin.  I can now feel a sort of calling not just in my dreams, but in my waking moments, too.  Stopping to take a swallow from a flask of water, I note my provisions are getting low.  I will be arriving in Qeynos just in time.  Still, this is all I can afford with the meager money I have.<br>
<br>
The guard tower that watches the pass from Qeynos Hills to the plains of Karana looms overhead.  A pair of guards man it, both of their eyes fixed on me as I pass.  One of them is a muscular shapely figure with a hardened expression.  His hand rests on his sword, his whole body facing me, as if he is saying just give me a reason not to let you pass.  The other guard is a little bit plumper, and while he wears the same uniform, his is adorned in a few jewels here and there.  He is more relaxed, and is only casually watching me, going through the motions of guarding, but not really seeming to be present here.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  The days events are all quite so confusing.  This afternoon while I was arriving in Qeynos, I felt sure that I needed to go to Erudin to get my question answered.  Now I’m not sure.  As soon as I arrived in Qeynos I had doubts about my plan.  Was my plan wrong to begin with, and I was supposed to go to Qeynos?  Whatever gods there may be, Karana or otherwise, seem to want me to stay.  I went to the dock to inquire about when the boat would be leaving for Odus.  There was a friendly gnome there who said he was from the Academy of Arcane Sciences.  Apparently the boats are having trouble, and he recommended I check back in the morning, and that they were working on getting some sort of transportation in place, whatever that means.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
I pass through the gates under the watchful eyes of more guards.  There are a few gnolls about trying to break past defenses, so they are not paying quite as much attention to me.  Past the gates, I turn the corner and find a pub.  Now seems as good a time as any.  I glance up at the sign as I push open the door.  “…<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  A crow caws three times</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->…”  Crows Pub and Casino.  Just inside the door is a painting of  crows playing poker.  Sitting at the bar, I order ale.  The bartender asks for payment in advance, so I glance around and find some unattended payment while his back is turned.  He sets down a napkin and places a glass of ale on it, giving me a dirty look as he picks up the coin to inspect it, before shoving it in his pocket.<br>
<br>
The grass is quickly drained and I pick up the napkin to wipe the foam off my face.  Just then I notice a message scribbled on the back: <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  An unseen hand from the shadows beckons you into the darkness.  Hanns Krieghor has need of your skills.  Take this note to Hanns, and he shall instruct you further.  Go to Crow’s.  Your entryway into the unseen lies behind the painting.  Tread carefully, the obvious path is the wrong one.  Feel the walls for safe passage to the hideout</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Glancing up, the bartender is busy wiping off glasses, not paying any attention to me.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Everything that has transpired this afternoon feel like puzzle pieces that have been falling into place.  The pub, the feeling, the boats.  And I’ve been thinking about what the farmer said about Karana the other day.  I’ve never really thought much about the gods.  Perhaps it is time I started thinking about more than just myself.  Or perhaps not.  But I am here for a reason, I am sure.  I just don’t know what yet.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
The passage was dark and damp, lit only by a few torches.  Finding the entryway behind the painting was tricky, but fortunately it was in a private room so I had time to analyze it.  Following the path I almost mis-stepped,, falling into a hidden pit.  The obvious path is the wrong path indeed.  I backtracked a few steps and found a spot in the wall where the bricks could be moved just enough to slip through.  A false wall of sorts.  I went in and found a man standing there who must have been Hanns Krieghor.  He looked at me with an accusing glance, declaring “Lucky thing you weren’t followed, or you’d be breathing through holes in your back right now.”  Charming.<br>
<br>
I explained him about the bartender and showed him the napkin.  He explained that he’d gotten word of me when I passed through High Hold Keep.  He could use someone who could slip in and out of shadows as I could.  However, he said my skills were poor.  What flatter.  He offered to help train me in the ways of the Circle of the Unseen Hand.  He also called me a sewer crawled, again flattered I’m sure.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Perhaps this is the end of my journey.  I still need time to wrap myself around everything that has happened today.  Tomorrow will bring another day, another end, another beginning, and maybe some answers.  But until then, I sleep.<br>
<br>
This night brings me a fresh awakening, and no dream.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
