s the dune.  I almost did not hear it in the wind, and thought the heat was getting to me.  But there it is again.  Following the voice to where it was coming from I find a little gnome standing on the platform the wizards use.<br>
<br>
Others followed the calls as well and are now gathered around.  Finally with the crowd about and curios, the gnome speaks.  He proclaims that he was working on the ultimate clockwork.  He was nearly done.  However he needs the chitin from the tarantulas that roams the dunes to complete it.  A few disperse, off scouting for the tarantulas at that point.  I will admit I am curious about the clockwork.  I had heard of the gnomes before but never seen their work up close.  But curiosity is not enough for me to go roaming across the desert after some overgrown spider.  The gnome offers to pay, however.  That is enough for me, and I set out, joining the others hunting down the spiders.<br>
<br>
The spiders had apparently scattered from all the commotion, but after some scouting I am able to find one.  Quickly dispatching it, I bring back part of it to the gnome, who offers payment in return.  The gnome says he still needs more and would buy all I could get.  So once again I set out, find some spiders and gathered their chitin.  However when I get back the gnome was gone.<br>
<br>
Others were also gathered around, their spider chitin ready to sell to the gnome.  The lousy footrest ran off and did not buy all the chitin he said he would.  I curse into the wind and prepare to once again set off after my mark, when I hear the same voice in the distance again, and some clanging metal.  More clanging, and some curses.  I try to find out where the voice is coming from, but the entire desert has gone silent.<br>
<br>
Then I see it.  A monstrous metal spider comes stomping through the desert, straight at the crowd of onlookers.  However it quickly becomes apparent it is not there for a show.  This thing wants destruction.  Of all the stories I have heard of gnomes, I had heard none of them being destructive like this.  Several fall to it’s attack, and then it turns towards me.  I try to stop it, but my blade is no match for the metal.  It is the best I can do just to not get hit too bad.<br>
<br>
I run off to get help, but I scarcely get a dune away when help arrives uncalled.  One more skilled than myself arrives and is able to take care of the spider.  However, no sign of the gnome to be found.<br>
<br>
Those gnomes are not to be trusted if they unleash such as this on the world.  Perhaps it is time for a trip to Ak’anon to try and track this gnome down and show him his mistake.<br>
 <p>Mithlin<BR>
